<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>William P. Favorite was a graduate in chemical engineering at the University of Michigan, class of 1920.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The William P. Favorite collection contains material relating to reunions of the 1917 and 1920 graduating classes of the School of Engineering at the University of Michigan; records, 1941-1962, of Radio Construction Company, including material related to the construction of the University of Michigan's Peach Mountain Radio Astronomy Observatory; and collected material relating to the history of Favorite's home town of Sturgis, Michigan.</p>
</scopecontent>

